<p valign="top">GETNAME(2) avr-Xinu GETNAME(2)</p>

<p style="margin-top: 1em" valign="top"><b>NAME</b></p>

<p style="margin-left:8%;">getname &minus; return the
official Internet domain name of the local host</p>


<p style="margin-top: 1em" valign="top"><b>SYNOPSIS</b></p>

<p style="margin-left:8%;"><i>int *getname(name) <br>
char *name;</i></p>


<p style="margin-top: 1em" valign="top"><b>DESCRIPTION</b></p>

<p style="margin-left:8%;"><i>Getname</i> returns the
least&minus;significant component of the official Internet
domain name of the local host using GETADDR(2) to obtain the
host&rsquo;s IP address, and IP2NAME(2) to translate the IP
address into a domain name. For example, when executed on
host <i>merlin.cs.purdue.edu</i>, <i>getname</i> returns the
string <i>merlin</i>.</p>

<p style="margin-left:8%; margin-top: 1em">Argument
<i>name</i> gives the starting address of an area in which
the name should be placed. <i>Getname</i> writes the name as
a contiguous, null&minus;terminated byte string.</p>

<p style="margin-top: 1em" valign="top"><b>SEE ALSO</b></p>

<p style="margin-left:8%;">ip2name(2), getaddr(2)</p>

<p style="margin-top: 1em" valign="top"><b>BUGS</b></p>

<p style="margin-left:8%;">There is no way to force
<i>getname</i> to return the full domain name.</p>

<p style="margin-left:8%; margin-top: 1em">XINU V7
February&nbsp;8, 2011 XINU V7</p>
